wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant John Herbert Greenwood Womersley  (1 April 1896 – 23 January 1962) was a World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories.

response: During the course of the war, ten aces served in the squadron, including Henry Woollett, Cecil Frederick King, John Lightfoot Trollope, Geoffrey Bailey, Harold Balfour, Charles C. Banks, Hector Daniel, George Lingham, and John Womersley. ( Robert Johnstone Owen).
